VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'That was my playground. &gt;&gt; [music] &gt;&gt; That is where I learned to take the wild stuff floating around inside my head and turn it into something you can actually play. And that [music] one word, imagination,'

[01:05] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'turned out to be the whole key. Because only when I taught imagination to the AI, did I finally hit my breakthrough. Only then did I actually manage to make a game [music] with it.'

[01:17] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'So, I took that imagination trained AI, and I wrapped it up in a tool with a sweet little name. Mirakit. And the best part, it is fully open source, free for'

[01:29] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'everyone, so you can openly read on a technical level exactly how I implemented imagination into a large language model. And trust me, this part matters more than anything else. Because before this,'

[01:42] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'I was just going in circles, chatting with the model, asking for game [music] code, and the code kept spitting out more bugs, more misunderstandings, more mess.'

[01:54] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'It was only when I added imagination that I got real progress. So, what does imagination actually look like for an AI? It takes your prompt, it looks at the whole project, the full context, and it imagines how the thing should correctly'

[02:06] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'look, and how to technically pull it off. Because here is the honest truth. What you write and how you write it in chat is not always correct. A language model will follow your order unconditionally,'

[02:19] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'and most of the time it will break things instead of fixing them. Imagination gives it a direction. And yes, sometimes it changes what you asked for, but it changes it out of consequence and verification, not at random.'

[02:33] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'And that, my friend, is exactly the effect you want. So, I made my game, and this time it came to life in a single rainy day. It is called Cat Volleyball. And actually, before I say another word'

